Claim: "A crowded dock has people on it."
Implication: "A crowded dock has people standing next to a freight car."
Referring expressions: A crowded dock, people  A crowded dock, people, freight car
Formula: (exists a (IsCrowded(a) and HasPeople(a)) & (forall e (forall d ( IsStandingNextTo(d,e) ->   HasPeople(d))))) -> (exists a (exists b (IsStandingNextTo(a,b) and IsOnFreightCar(a))))
